# .shhhignore - Ignore rules for shhh secret scanner
#
# Place this file as .shhhignore in your project root or in ~/.config/shhh/.shhhignore
# for global rules. Both locations are loaded and merged.
#
# Format: one rule per line.
# Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored.

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Literal strings
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# If a literal string appears in a finding's match or context, skip it.
# Useful for known-safe tokens or test fixtures.
#
# ghp_abc123exampleTestToken
# AKIAIOSFODNN7EXAMPLE

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Secret type prefixes (type:)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Skip all findings whose secretType starts with the given prefix.
# Case-insensitive matching.
#
# type:High-Entropy
# type:Generic API Key
# type:JWT

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# File path globs (file:)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Skip files whose absolute path matches the glob pattern.
# Uses standard glob syntax (** for recursive match).
#
# file:**/test-fixtures/**
# file:**/archived_sessions/**
# file:**/*.test.json

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Platform exclusions (platform:)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Skip an entire platform's findings. Valid values: claude, codex, copilot.
#
# platform:copilot
